name: aws-workbench
description: Your complete AWS toolkit, right in VS Code

commands.title: Aws Access:Test Aws Connectivity With Active User
Aws Access:Copy Credentials To Default Profile

view/item/context.when: view == SqsTreeView && (viewItem == Queue || viewItem == Queue || viewItem == PublishAdhoc || viewItem == PublishFile)
view == SnsTreeView && (viewItem == Topic || viewItem == Topic || viewItem == PublishAdhoc || viewItem == PublishFile)

view == StepFuncTreeView && (viewItem == StepFunc || viewItem == TriggerConfig || viewItem == TriggerSavedPayload || viewItem == TriggerWithPayload || viewItem == TriggerFilePayload || viewItem == TriggerNoPayload)

view == LambdaTreeView && (viewItem == Lambda || viewItem == TriggerConfig || viewItem == TriggerSavedPayload || viewItem == TriggerWithPayload || viewItem == TriggerFilePayload || viewItem == TriggerNoPayload)

viewsWelcome.contents:
Please click [+] to add your buckets. 
 [Add Bucket](command:S3TreeView.AddBucket) 
 Leave bucket name empty to get all your buckets. You can enter bucket name partially. 
 If you can not connect after a while check your Aws Credentials, Network and Proxy settings. 



 To Access Aws, you need to configure aws credentials. 
 For more detail on Aws Credentials [Click Here](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-configure-files.html) 
 For a Youtube Tutorial [Click Here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SON8sY1iOBU) 
 [Test Aws Connection](command:S3TreeView.TestAwsConnection) 
 [Update Aws EndPoint](command:S3TreeView.UpdateAwsEndPoint)

Please click [+] to add your SQS Queue. 
 [Add Queue](command:SqsTreeView.AddQueue) 
 Leave Queue name empty to get all your topics. You can enter queue name partially.

 To Access Aws, you need to configure aws credentials. 
 For more detail on Aws Credentials [Click Here](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-configure-files.html)
